54 qboolean G_MatchOnePlayer(int *plist, char *err, size_t len)
55 {
56  err[0] = '\0';
57 
58  if (plist[0] == -1)
59  {
60  Q_strcat(err, len, "no connected player by that name or slot #");
61  return qfalse;
62  }
63  if (plist[1] != -1)
64  {
65  char line[MAX_NAME_LENGTH + 10];
66  gclient_t *cl;
67  int *p;
68 
69  line[0] = '\0';
70 
71  Q_strcat(err, len, "more than one player name matches be more specific or use the slot #:\n");
72  for (p = plist; *p != -1; p++)
73  {
74  cl = &level.clients[*p];
75  if (cl->pers.connected == CON_CONNECTED)
76  {
77  Com_sprintf(line, MAX_NAME_LENGTH + 10, "%2i - %s^7\n", *p, cl->pers.netname);
78  if (strlen(err) + strlen(line) > len)
79  {
80  break;
81  }
82  Q_strcat(err, len, line);
83  }
84  }
85  return qfalse;
86  }
87  return qtrue;
88 }

98 int ClientNumbersFromString(char *s, int *plist)
99 {
100  gclient_t *p;
101  int i, found = 0;
102  char s2[MAX_STRING_CHARS];
103  char n2[MAX_STRING_CHARS];
104  char *m;
105  char *end = NULL;
106 
107  *plist = -1;
108 
109  // if a number is provided, it might be a slot #
110  // check the whole string is a number and only if so assume it is a slot number
111  // still fails for players with a name like "23" and there are 24 slots used
112  i = (int) strtol(s, &end, 10); // end will be "" when s contains only digits
113 
114  if ((!end || !*end) && i >= 0)
115  {
116  if (i >= 0 && i < level.maxclients)
117  {
118  p = &level.clients[i];
119  if (p->pers.connected == CON_CONNECTED || p->pers.connected == CON_CONNECTING)
120  {
121  *plist++ = i;
122  *plist = -1;
123  return 1;
124  }
125  }
126  }
127 
128  // now look for name matches
129  SanitizeString(s, s2, qtrue);
130  if (strlen(s2) < 1)
131  {
132  return 0;
133  }
134  for (i = 0; i < level.maxclients; ++i)
135  {
136  p = &level.clients[i];
137  if (p->pers.connected != CON_CONNECTED && p->pers.connected != CON_CONNECTING)
138  {
139 
140  continue;
141  }
142  SanitizeString(p->pers.netname, n2, qtrue);
143  m = strstr(n2, s2);
144  if (m != NULL)
145  {
146  *plist++ = i;
147  found++;
148  }
149  }
150  *plist = -1;
151  return found;
152 }

185 void G_PlaySound_Cmd(void)
186 {
187  char sound[MAX_QPATH], name[MAX_NAME_LENGTH], cmd[32] = { "playsound" };
188 
189  if (trap_Argc() < 2)
190  {
191  G_Printf("usage: playsound [name|slot#] sound\n");
192  return;
193  }
194 
195  if (trap_Argc() > 2)
196  {
197  trap_Argv(0, cmd, sizeof(cmd));
198  trap_Argv(1, name, sizeof(name));
199  trap_Argv(2, sound, sizeof(sound));
200  }
201  else
202  {
203  trap_Argv(1, sound, sizeof(sound));
204  name[0] = '\0';
205  }
206 
207  if (name[0])
208  {
209  int pids[MAX_CLIENTS];
210  char err[MAX_STRING_CHARS];
211  gentity_t *victim;
212 
213  if (ClientNumbersFromString(name, pids) != 1)
214  {
215  G_MatchOnePlayer(pids, err, sizeof(err));
216  G_Printf("playsound: %s\n", err);
217  return;
218  }
219  victim = &level.gentities[pids[0]];
220 
221  if (!Q_stricmp(cmd, "playsound_env"))
222  {
223  G_AddEvent(victim, EV_GENERAL_SOUND, G_SoundIndex(sound));
224  }
225  else
226  {
227  G_ClientSound(victim, G_SoundIndex(sound));
228  }
229  }
230  else
231  {
232  G_globalSound(sound);
233  }
234 }

289 qboolean G_SendScore_Add(gentity_t *ent, int i, char *buf, int bufsize)
290 {
291  gclient_t *cl = &level.clients[level.sortedClients[i]];
292  int ping, respawnsLeft = cl->ps.persistant[PERS_RESPAWNS_LEFT]; // number of respawns left
293  char entry[128];
294  int totalXP = 0;
295  int miscFlags = 0; // 1 - ready 2 - is bot
296 
297  entry[0] = '\0';
298 
299  if (g_gametype.integer == GT_WOLF_LMS)
300  {
301  if (g_entities[level.sortedClients[i]].health <= 0)
302  {
303  respawnsLeft = -2;
304  }
305  }
306  else if (respawnsLeft == 0 && ((cl->ps.pm_flags & PMF_LIMBO) || (level.intermissiontime && g_entities[level.sortedClients[i]].health <= 0)))
307  {
308  respawnsLeft = -2;
309  }
310 
311  if (cl->pers.connected == CON_CONNECTING)
312  {
313  ping = -1;
314  }
315  else
316  {
317  ping = cl->ps.ping < 999 ? cl->ps.ping : 999;
318  }
319 
320  if (g_gametype.integer == GT_WOLF_LMS)
321  {
322  totalXP = cl->ps.persistant[PERS_SCORE];
323  }
324  else
325  {
326  int j;
327 
328  if ((g_gametype.integer == GT_WOLF_CAMPAIGN && (g_campaigns[level.currentCampaign].current != 0 && !level.newCampaign)) ||
329  (g_gametype.integer == GT_WOLF_LMS && g_currentRound.integer != 0))
330  {
331  for (j = SK_BATTLE_SENSE; j < SK_NUM_SKILLS; j++)
332  {
333  totalXP += cl->sess.skillpoints[j];
334  }
335  }
336  else
337  {
338  for (j = SK_BATTLE_SENSE; j < SK_NUM_SKILLS; j++)
339  {
340  // current map XPs only
341  totalXP += cl->sess.skillpoints[j] - cl->sess.startskillpoints[j];
342  }
343  }
344  }
345 
346  if (cl->ps.eFlags & EF_READY)
347  {
348  miscFlags |= 1;
349  }
350 
351  if (g_entities[level.sortedClients[i]].r.svFlags & SVF_BOT)
352  {
353  miscFlags |= 2;
354  }
355 
356  Com_sprintf(entry,
357  sizeof(entry),
358  " %i %i %i %i %i %i %i",
359  level.sortedClients[i],
360  totalXP,
361  ping,
362  (level.intermissiontime - cl->pers.enterTime) / 60000,
363  g_entities[level.sortedClients[i]].s.powerups,
364  miscFlags,
365  respawnsLeft
366  );
367 
368  if ((strlen(buf) + strlen(entry) + 1) > bufsize)
369  {
370  return qfalse;
371  }
372  Q_strcat(buf, bufsize, entry);
373 
374  return qtrue;
375 }

381 void G_SendScore(gentity_t *ent)
382 {
383  int i = 0;
384  int numSorted = level.numConnectedClients; // send the latest information on all clients
385  int count = 0;
386  // commands over 1022 will crash the client so they're
387  // pruned in trap_SendServerCommand()
388  // 1022 -32 for the startbuffer -3 for the clientNum
389  char buffer[987];
390  char startbuffer[32];
391 
392  *buffer = '\0';
393  *startbuffer = '\0';
394 
395 #ifdef FEATURE_RATING
396  if (g_skillRating.integer)
397  {
398  G_SendSkillRating(ent);
399  }
400 #endif
401 
402  Q_strncpyz(startbuffer, va(
403  "sc0 %i %i",
404  level.teamScores[TEAM_AXIS],
405  level.teamScores[TEAM_ALLIES]),
406  sizeof(startbuffer));
407 
408  // keep adding scores to the sc0 command until we fill
409  // up the buffer. Any scores that are left will be
410  // added on to the sc1 command.
411  for (; i < numSorted; ++i)
412  {
413  // the old version of SendScore() did this. I removed it
414  // originally because it seemed like an unneccessary hack.
415  // perhaps it is necessary for compat with CG_Argv()?
416  if (count == 33)
417  {
418  break;
419  }
420  if (!G_SendScore_Add(ent, i, buffer, sizeof(buffer)))
421  {
422  break;
423  }
424  count++;
425  }
426  trap_SendServerCommand(ent - g_entities, va("%s %i%s", startbuffer, count, buffer));
427 
428  if (i == numSorted)
429  {
430  return;
431  }
432 
433  count = 0;
434  *buffer = '\0';
435  *startbuffer = '\0';
436  Q_strncpyz(startbuffer, "sc1", sizeof(startbuffer));
437  for (; i < numSorted; ++i)
438  {
439  if (!G_SendScore_Add(ent, i, buffer, sizeof(buffer)))
440  {
441  G_Printf("ERROR: G_SendScore() buffer overflow\n");
442  break;
443  }
444  count++;
445  }
446  if (!count)
447  {
448  return;
449  }
450 
451  trap_SendServerCommand(ent - g_entities, va("%s %i%s", startbuffer, count, buffer));
452 }

488 char *ConcatArgs(int start)
489 {
490  int i, c;
491  unsigned int tlen, len = 0;
492  static char line[MAX_STRING_CHARS];
493  char arg[MAX_STRING_CHARS];
494 
495  c = trap_Argc();
496  for (i = start ; i < c ; i++)
497  {
498  trap_Argv(i, arg, sizeof(arg));
499  tlen = strlen(arg);
500  if (len + tlen >= MAX_STRING_CHARS - 1)
501  {
502  break;
503  }
504  Com_Memcpy(line + len, arg, tlen);
505  len += tlen;
506  if (i != c - 1)
507  {
508  line[len] = ' ';
509  len++;
510  }
511  }
512 
513  line[len] = 0;
514 
515  return line;
516 }

524 void SanitizeString(char *in, char *out, qboolean fToLower)
525 {
526  while (*in)
527  {
528  if (*in == 27 || *in == '^')
529  {
530  in++; // skip color code
531  if (*in)
532  {
533  in++;
534  }
535  continue;
536  }
537 
538  if (*in < 32)
539  {
540  in++;
541  continue;
542  }
543 
544  *out++ = (fToLower) ? tolower(*in++) : *in++;
545  }
546 
547  *out = 0;
548 }

556 int ClientNumberFromString(gentity_t *to, char *s)
557 {
558  gclient_t *cl;
559  int idnum;
560  char s2[MAX_STRING_CHARS];
561  char n2[MAX_STRING_CHARS];
562  qboolean fIsNumber = qtrue;
563 
564  // See if its a number or string
565  for (idnum = 0; idnum < (int)strlen(s) && s[idnum] != 0; idnum++)
566  {
567  if (s[idnum] < '0' || s[idnum] > '9')
568  {
569  fIsNumber = qfalse;
570  break;
571  }
572  }
573 
574  // check for a name match
575  SanitizeString(s, s2, qtrue);
576  for (idnum = 0, cl = level.clients; idnum < level.maxclients; idnum++, cl++)
577  {
578  if (cl->pers.connected != CON_CONNECTED)
579  {
580  continue;
581  }
582 
583  SanitizeString(cl->pers.netname, n2, qtrue);
584  if (!strcmp(n2, s2))
585  {
586  return(idnum);
587  }
588  }
589 
590  // numeric values are just slot numbers
591  if (fIsNumber)
592  {
593  idnum = atoi(s);
594  if (idnum < 0 || idnum >= level.maxclients)
595  {
596  CPx(to - g_entities, va("print \"Bad client slot: [lof]%i\n\"", idnum));
597  return -1;
598  }
599 
600  cl = &level.clients[idnum];
601  if (cl->pers.connected != CON_CONNECTED)
602  {
603  CPx(to - g_entities, va("print \"Client[lof] %i [lon]is not active\n\"", idnum));
604  return -1;
605  }
606  return(idnum);
607  }
608 
609  CPx(to - g_entities, va("print \"User [lof]%s [lon]is not on the server\n\"", s));
610  return -1;
611 }

619 float GetSkillPointUntilLevelUp(gentity_t *ent, skillType_t skill)
620 {
621  if (ent->client->sess.skill[skill] < NUM_SKILL_LEVELS - 1)
622  {
623  int i = ent->client->sess.skill[skill] + 1;
624  int x = 1;
625 
626  for (; i < NUM_SKILL_LEVELS; i++, x++)
627  {
628  if (GetSkillTableData(skill)->skillLevels[ent->client->sess.skill[skill] + x] >= 0)
629  {
630  return GetSkillTableData(skill)->skillLevels[ent->client->sess.skill[skill] + x] - ent->client->sess.skillpoints[skill];
631  }
632  }
633  }
634  return -1;
635 }

751  }

787 
788  if (give_all || Q_stricmp(name, "weapons") == 0)

1197 void G_TeamDataForString(const char *teamstr, int clientNum, team_t *team, spectatorState_t *sState, int *specClient)
1198 {
1199  *sState = SPECTATOR_NOT;
1200  if (!Q_stricmp(teamstr, "follow1")) // follow player 1 as a spectator (we do require at least 1 playing client)
1201  {
1202  *team = TEAM_SPECTATOR;
1203  if (TeamCount(clientNum, TEAM_AXIS) + TeamCount(clientNum, TEAM_ALLIES) > 0)
1204  {
1205  *sState = SPECTATOR_FOLLOW;
1206  }
1207  else
1208  {
1209  *sState = SPECTATOR_FREE;
1210  }
1211 
1212  if (specClient)
1213  {
1214  *specClient = -1;
1215  }
1216  }
1217  else if (!Q_stricmp(teamstr, "follow2")) // follow player 2 as a spectator (we do require at least 2 playing clients)
1218  {
1219  int specClientNum = -2;
1220  int playerCount = TeamCount(clientNum, TEAM_AXIS) + TeamCount(clientNum, TEAM_ALLIES);
1221 
1222  *team = TEAM_SPECTATOR;
1223  if (playerCount > 1)
1224  {
1225  *sState = SPECTATOR_FOLLOW;
1226  }
1227  // if there is no 2nd player to follow, follow the first one
1228  else if (playerCount > 0)
1229  {
1230  *sState = SPECTATOR_FOLLOW;
1231  specClientNum = -1;
1232  }
1233  else
1234  {
1235  *sState = SPECTATOR_FREE;
1236  }
1237 
1238  if (specClient)
1239  {
1240  *specClient = specClientNum;
1241  }
1242  }
1243  else if (!Q_stricmp(teamstr, "spectator") || !Q_stricmp(teamstr, "s"))
1244  {
1245  *team = TEAM_SPECTATOR;
1246  *sState = SPECTATOR_FREE;
1247  }
1248  else if (!Q_stricmp(teamstr, "red") || !Q_stricmp(teamstr, "r") || !Q_stricmp(teamstr, "axis"))
1249  {
1250  *team = TEAM_AXIS;
1251  }
1252  else if (!Q_stricmp(teamstr, "blue") || !Q_stricmp(teamstr, "b") || !Q_stricmp(teamstr, "allies"))
1253  {
1254  *team = TEAM_ALLIES;
1255  }
1256  else
1257  {
1258  *team = PickTeam(clientNum);
1259  if (!G_teamJoinCheck(*team, &g_entities[clientNum]))
1260  {
1261  *team = ((TEAM_AXIS | TEAM_ALLIES) & ~*team);
1262  }
1263  }

1270 void G_DropItems(gentity_t *self)
1271 {
1272  gitem_t *item = NULL;
1273 
1274  // drop flag regardless
1275  if (self->client->ps.powerups[PW_REDFLAG])
1276  {
1277  item = BG_GetItem(ITEM_RED_FLAG);
1278  self->client->ps.powerups[PW_REDFLAG] = 0;
1279 
1280  // update objective indicator
1281  level.redFlagCounter -= 1;
1282  G_globalFlagIndicator();
1283  }
1284  if (self->client->ps.powerups[PW_BLUEFLAG])
1285  {
1286  item = BG_GetItem(ITEM_BLUE_FLAG);
1287  self->client->ps.powerups[PW_BLUEFLAG] = 0;
1288 
1289  // update objective indicator
1290  level.blueFlagCounter -= 1;
1291  G_globalFlagIndicator();
1292  }
1293 
1294  if (item)
1295  {
1296  vec3_t launchvel = { 0, 0, 0 };
1297  vec3_t forward;
1298  vec3_t origin;
1299  vec3_t angles;
1300  gentity_t *flag;
1301  vec3_t mins;
1302  vec3_t maxs;
1303  vec3_t viewpos;
1304  trace_t tr;
1305 
1306  VectorCopy(self->client->ps.origin, origin);
1307  // if the player hasn't died, then assume he's throwing objective
1308  if (self->health > 0)
1309  {
1310  VectorCopy(self->client->ps.viewangles, angles);
1311  if (angles[PITCH] > 0)
1312  {
1313  angles[PITCH] = 0;
1314  }
1315  AngleVectors(angles, forward, NULL, NULL);
1316  VectorMA(self->client->ps.velocity, 96, forward, launchvel);
1317  VectorMA(origin, 36.0f, forward, origin);
1318  origin[2] += self->client->ps.viewheight;
1319 
1320  // prevent stuck item in solid
1321  VectorCopy(self->client->ps.origin, viewpos);
1322  VectorSet(mins, -(ITEM_RADIUS + 8), -(ITEM_RADIUS + 8), 0);
1323  VectorSet(maxs, (ITEM_RADIUS + 8), (ITEM_RADIUS + 8), 2 * (ITEM_RADIUS + 8));
1324 
1325  trap_EngineerTrace(&tr, viewpos, mins, maxs, origin, self->s.number, MASK_MISSILESHOT);
1326  if (tr.startsolid)
1327  {
1328  VectorCopy(forward, viewpos);
1329  VectorNormalizeFast(viewpos);
1330  VectorMA(self->r.currentOrigin, -24.f, viewpos, viewpos);
1331 
1332  trap_EngineerTrace(&tr, viewpos, mins, maxs, origin, self->s.number, MASK_MISSILESHOT);
1333 
1334  VectorCopy(tr.endpos, origin);
1335  }
1336  else if (tr.fraction < 1) // oops, bad launch spot
1337  {
1338  VectorCopy(tr.endpos, origin);
1339  SnapVectorTowards(origin, viewpos);
1340  }
1341 
1342  // set timer
1343  self->client->dropObjectiveTime = level.time;
1344  }
1345 
1346  flag = LaunchItem(item, origin, launchvel, self->s.number);
1347 
1348  flag->s.modelindex2 = self->s.otherEntityNum2; // FIXME set player->otherentitynum2 with old modelindex2 from flag and restore here
1349  flag->message = self->message; // also restore item name
1350 
1351 #ifdef OMNIBOTS
1352  Bot_Util_SendTrigger(flag, NULL, va("%s dropped.", flag->message), "dropped");
1353 #endif
1354  // Clear out player's temp copies
1355  self->s.otherEntityNum2 = 0;
1356  self->message = NULL;
1357  }
1358 }

1370 qboolean SetTeam(gentity_t *ent, const char *s, qboolean force, weapon_t w1, weapon_t w2, qboolean setweapons)
1371 {

1378 
1379  // see what change is requested
1380

1382 
1383  if (ent->client->freezed)
1384  {
1385  trap_SendServerCommand(clientNum, "cp \"You are frozen!\n\"");
1386  return qfalse;
1387  }
1388 
1389  if (team != TEAM_SPECTATOR)
1390  {
1391  // Ensure the player can join
1392  if (!G_teamJoinCheck(team, ent))
1393  {
1394  // Leave them where they were before the command was issued
1395  return qfalse;
1396  }
1397

1399  {
1400  trap_SendServerCommand(clientNum, "cp \"You cannot switch during a match, please wait until the round ends.\"");
1401  return qfalse; // ignore the request
1402  }
1403 
1404  if (((g_gametype.integer == GT_WOLF_LMS && g_lms_teamForceBalance.integer) || g_teamForceBalance.integer) && !force)
1405  {
1406  int counts[TEAM_NUM_TEAMS];
1407 
1408  counts[TEAM_ALLIES] = TeamCount(ent - g_entities, TEAM_ALLIES);
1409  counts[TEAM_AXIS] = TeamCount(ent - g_entities, TEAM_AXIS);
1410 
1411  // We allow a spread of one
1412  if (team == TEAM_AXIS && counts[TEAM_AXIS] - counts[TEAM_ALLIES] >= 1)
1413  {
1414  CP("cp \"The Axis has too many players.\n\"");
1415  return qfalse; // ignore the request
1416  }
1417  if (team == TEAM_ALLIES && counts[TEAM_ALLIES] - counts[TEAM_AXIS] >= 1)
1418  {
1419  CP("cp \"The Allies have too many players.\n\"");
1420  return qfalse; // ignore the request
1421  }
1422 
1423  // It's ok, the team we are switching to has less or same number of players
1424  }
1425  }
1426 
1427  if (g_maxGameClients.integer > 0 && level.numNonSpectatorClients >= g_maxGameClients.integer)
1428  {
1429  team = TEAM_SPECTATOR;
1430  }
1431 
1432  // decide if we will allow the change
1433  oldTeam = client->sess.sessionTeam;
1434  if (team == oldTeam && team != TEAM_SPECTATOR)
1435  {
1436  return qfalse;
1437  }
1438 
1439  // prevent players from switching to regain deployments
1440  if (g_gametype.integer != GT_WOLF_LMS)
1441  {
1442  if ((g_maxlives.integer > 0 ||
1443  (g_alliedmaxlives.integer > 0 && ent->client->sess.sessionTeam == TEAM_ALLIES) ||
1444  (g_axismaxlives.integer > 0 && ent->client->sess.sessionTeam == TEAM_AXIS)) &&
1445  ent->client->ps.persistant[PERS_RESPAWNS_LEFT] == 0 && oldTeam != TEAM_SPECTATOR)
1446  {
1447  if (g_gamestate.integer == GS_PLAYING) // but allow changing team in warmup
1448  {
1449  CP("cp \"You can't switch teams because you are out of lives.\n\" 3");

1451  }
1452  }
1453  }
1454 
1455  // execute the team change
1456  if (team != TEAM_SPECTATOR)
1457  {
1458  client->pers.initialSpawn = qfalse;
1459 #ifdef FEATURE_MULTIVIEW
1460  // no MV in-game
1461  if (client->pers.mvCount > 0)
1462  {
1463  G_smvRemoveInvalidClients(ent, TEAM_AXIS);
1464  G_smvRemoveInvalidClients(ent, TEAM_ALLIES);

1467  }
1468 
1469  if (oldTeam != TEAM_SPECTATOR)
1470  {
1471  if (!(ent->client->ps.pm_flags & PMF_LIMBO))
1472  {
1473  // Kill him (makes sure he loses flags, etc)
1474  ent->flags &= ~FL_GODMODE;
1475  ent->client->ps.stats[STAT_HEALTH] = ent->health = 0;
1476  player_die(ent, ent, ent, 100000, MOD_SWITCHTEAM);
1477  }
1478  }
1479  // they go to the end of the line for tournements
1480  if (team == TEAM_SPECTATOR)
1481  {
1482  client->sess.spectatorTime = level.time;
1483  if (!client->sess.referee)
1484  {
1485  client->pers.invite = 0;
1486  }

1489  {
1490  G_smvAllRemoveSingleClient(ent - g_entities);
1491  }
1492 #endif
1493  }
1494 
1495  G_LeaveTank(ent, qfalse);
1496  G_RemoveClientFromFireteams(clientNum, qtrue, qfalse);
1497  if (g_landminetimeout.integer)
1498  {
1499  G_ExplodeMines(ent);
1500  }
1501  G_FadeItems(ent, MOD_SATCHEL);
1502

1504  {
1505  int i;
1506  mapEntityData_t *mEnt;
1507  mapEntityData_Team_t *teamList;
1508

1510  {
1511  teamList = &mapEntityData[i];

1514  {

1516  }

1522  mapEntityData_t *mEntFree = mEnt;
1523

1525

1527  }
1528  }

1530  client->sess.spec_team = 0;
1531  client->sess.sessionTeam = team;
1532  client->sess.spectatorState = specState;
1533  client->sess.spectatorClient = specClient;
1534  client->pers.ready = qfalse;
1535 
1536  // During team switching you can sometime spawn immediately
1537  client->pers.lastReinforceTime = 0;
1538 
1539  // (l)users will spam spec messages... honest!
1540  if (team != oldTeam)
1541  {
1542  gentity_t *tent = G_PopupMessage(PM_TEAM);
1543 
1544  tent->s.effect2Time = team;
1545  tent->s.effect3Time = clientNum;
1546  tent->s.density = 0;
1547  }

1552  }

1556  ClientUserinfoChanged(clientNum);
1557

1559 
1560  // restore old respawn count (players cannot jump from team to team to regain lives)

1563  client->ps.persistant[PERS_RESPAWNS_LEFT] = respawnsLeft;
1564  }

1802 qboolean G_IsWeaponDisabled(gentity_t *ent, weapon_t weapon)
1803 {
1804  int playerCount, weaponCount, maxCount = -1;
1805  const char *weaponString;
1806 
1807  // allow selecting weapons as spectator for bots (to avoid endless loops in pfnChangeTeam())
1808  if (ent->client->sess.sessionTeam == TEAM_SPECTATOR && !(ent->r.svFlags & SVF_BOT))
1809  {
1810  return qtrue;
1811  }
1812 
1813  if (!(GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->skillBased == SK_HEAVY_WEAPONS || (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_RIFLENADE)
1814  || (GetWeaponTableData(GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->weapAlts)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_RIFLENADE)))
1815  {
1816  return qfalse;
1817  }
1818 
1819  playerCount = G_TeamCount(ent, -1);
1820  weaponCount = G_TeamCount(ent, weapon);
1821 
1822  // total percentage restriction
1823  if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->skillBased == SK_HEAVY_WEAPONS && weaponCount >= ceil(playerCount * g_heavyWeaponRestriction.integer * 0.01))
1824  {
1825  return qtrue;
1826  }
1827 
1828  // single weapon restrictions
1829  if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_PANZER)
1830  {
1831  maxCount = team_maxRockets.integer;
1832  weaponString = team_maxRockets.string;
1833  }
1834  else if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_MG)
1835  {
1836  maxCount = team_maxMachineguns.integer;
1837  weaponString = team_maxMachineguns.string;
1838  }
1839  else if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_MORTAR)
1840  {
1841  maxCount = team_maxMortars.integer;
1842  weaponString = team_maxMortars.string;
1843  }
1844  else if ((GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_RIFLENADE)
1845  || (GetWeaponTableData(GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->weapAlts)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_RIFLENADE))
1846  {
1847  maxCount = team_maxRiflegrenades.integer;
1848  weaponString = team_maxRiflegrenades.string;
1849  }
1850  else if (weapon == WP_FLAMETHROWER)
1851  {
1852  maxCount = team_maxFlamers.integer;
1853  weaponString = team_maxFlamers.string;
1854  }
1855 
1856  if (maxCount == -1)
1857  {
1858  return qfalse;
1859  }
1860 
1861  if (strstr(weaponString, "%-"))
1862  {
1863  maxCount = floor(maxCount * playerCount * 0.01);
1864  }
1865  else if (strstr(weaponString, "%"))
1866  {
1867  maxCount = ceil(maxCount * playerCount * 0.01);
1868  }
1869 
1870  if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->weapAlts)
1871  {
1872  // add basic weapons
1873  weaponCount += G_TeamCount(ent, GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->weapAlts);
1874  }
1875 
1876  if (weaponCount >= maxCount)
1877  {
1878  if (ent->client->ps.pm_flags & PMF_LIMBO)
1879  {
1880  CP(va("cp \"^1*^3 %s not available!^1 *\" 1", GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->desc));
1881  }
1882  return qtrue;
1883  }
1884 
1885  return qfalse;
1886 }

4074 qboolean G_PushPlayer(gentity_t *ent, gentity_t *victim)
4075 {
4076  vec3_t dir, push;
4077 
4078  if (!g_shove.integer)
4079  {
4080  return qfalse;
4081  }
4082 
4083  if (ent->health <= 0)
4084  {
4085  return qfalse;
4086  }
4087 
4088  if ((level.time - ent->client->pmext.shoveTime) < 500)
4089  {
4090  return qfalse;
4091  }
4092 
4093  // Prevent possible cheating, as well as annoying push after revive and spawning
4094  if (ent->client->ps.powerups[PW_INVULNERABLE])
4095  {
4096  return qfalse;
4097  }
4098 
4099  // if a player cannot move at this moment, don't allow him to get pushed..
4100  if (victim->client->ps.pm_flags & PMF_TIME_LOCKPLAYER)
4101  {
4102  return qfalse;
4103  }
4104 
4105  // Don't allow pushing when player is using mg
4106  if (victim->client->ps.persistant[PERS_HWEAPON_USE])
4107  {
4108  return qfalse;
4109  }
4110 
4111  ent->client->pmext.shoveTime = level.time;
4112 
4113  // push is our forward vector
4114  AngleVectors(ent->client->ps.viewangles, dir, NULL, NULL);
4115  VectorNormalizeFast(dir);
4116 
4117  // etpro velocity
4118  VectorScale(dir, g_shove.integer * 5, push);
4119 
4120  // no longer try to shove into ground
4121  if ((push[2] > Q_fabs(push[0])) &&
4122  (push[2] > Q_fabs(push[1])))
4123  {
4124  // player is being boosted
4125  if (g_misc.integer & G_MISC_SHOVE_Z)
4126  {
4127  // like in etpro, shoving up gives a bit more than JUMP_VELOCITY
4128  push[2] = dir[2] * g_shove.integer * 5;
4129  }
4130  else
4131  {
4132  push[2] = 64;
4133  }
4134  }
4135  else
4136  {
4137  // give them a little hop
4138  push[2] = 64;
4139  }
4140 
4141  VectorAdd(victim->s.pos.trDelta, push, victim->s.pos.trDelta);
4142  VectorAdd(victim->client->ps.velocity, push,
4143  victim->client->ps.velocity);
4144 
4145  // are we pushed?
4146  victim->client->pmext.shoved = qtrue;
4147  victim->client->pmext.pusher = ent - g_entities;
4148 
4149  G_AddEvent(victim, EV_SHOVE_SOUND, 0);
4150 
4151  victim->client->ps.pm_time = 100;
4152  victim->client->ps.pm_flags |= PMF_TIME_KNOCKBACK;
4153 
4154  return qtrue;
4155 }

4527 void G_CalcClientAccuracies(void)
4528 {
4529  int i, j;
4530  int shots, hits, headshots;
4531 
4532  for (i = 0; i < g_maxclients.integer; i++)
4533  {
4534  shots = 0;
4535  hits = 0;
4536  headshots = 0;
4537 
4538  if (g_entities[i].inuse)
4539  {
4540  for (j = 0; j < WS_MAX; j++)
4541  {
4542  // don't take into account weapon that can't do headshot
4543  if (!aWeaponInfo[j].fHasHeadShots)
4544  {
4545  continue;
4546  }
4547 
4548  shots += level.clients[i].sess.aWeaponStats[j].atts;
4549  hits += level.clients[i].sess.aWeaponStats[j].hits;
4550  headshots += level.clients[i].sess.aWeaponStats[j].headshots;
4551  }
4552 
4553  level.clients[i].acc = shots ? 100 * hits / (float)shots : 0.f;
4554  level.clients[i].hspct = hits ? 100 * headshots / (float)hits : 0.f;
4555  }
4556  else
4557  {
4558  level.clients[i].acc = 0.f;
4559  level.clients[i].hspct = 0.f;
4560  }
4561  }
4562 }

4600 void Cmd_SelectedObjective_f(gentity_t *ent)
4601 {
4602  int i, val;
4603  char buffer[16];
4604  vec_t dist, neardist = 0;
4605  int nearest = -1;
4606 
4607  if (!ent || !ent->client)
4608  {
4609  return;
4610  }
4611 
4612  if (trap_Argc() != 2)
4613  {
4614  return;
4615  }
4616  trap_Argv(1, buffer, 16);
4617  val = atoi(buffer) + 1;
4618 
4619  for (i = 0; i < level.numLimboCams; i++)
4620  {
4621  if (!level.limboCams[i].spawn && level.limboCams[i].info == val)
4622  {

4624  {

4628

4645  i = nearest;
4646 
4647  VectorCopy(level.limboCams[i].origin, ent->s.origin2);
4648  ent->r.svFlags |= SVF_SELF_PORTAL_EXCLUSIVE;
4649  trap_SendServerCommand(ent - g_entities, va("portalcampos %i %i %i %i %i %i %i %i", val - 1, (int)level.limboCams[i].origin[0], (int)level.limboCams[i].origin[1], (int)level.limboCams[i].origin[2], (int)level.limboCams[i].angles[0], (int)level.limboCams[i].angles[1], (int)level.limboCams[i].angles[2], level.limboCams[i].hasEnt ? level.limboCams[i].targetEnt : -1));

4713 void Cmd_SwapPlacesWithBot_f(gentity_t *ent, int botNum)
4714 {

4716  gclient_t cl, *client = ent->client;

4718  clientSession_t sess;

4720 
4721  if (!botent->client)

4724  }

4726  if (botent->health <= 0 && (botent->client->ps.pm_flags & PMF_LIMBO))
4727  {

4729  return;
4730  }
4731 
4732  if (client->sess.sessionTeam != botent->client->sess.sessionTeam)
4733  {
4734  trap_SendServerCommand(ent - g_entities, "print \"Bot is on different team, cannot swap places.\n\"");
4735  return;

4737 
4738  // copy the client information
4739  cl = *botent->client;
4740 
4741  G_DPrintf("Swapping places: %s in for %s\n", ent->client->pers.netname, botent->client->pers.netname);
4742  // kill the bot
4743  botent->flags &= ~FL_GODMODE;
4744  botent->client->ps.stats[STAT_HEALTH] = botent->health = 0;
4745  player_die(botent, ent, ent, 100000, MOD_SWAP_PLACES);
4746  // make sure they go into limbo mode right away, and dont show a corpse
4747  limbo(botent, qfalse);
4748  // respawn the player
4749  ent->client->ps.pm_flags &= ~PMF_LIMBO; // turns off limbo
4750  // copy the location
4751  VectorCopy(cl.ps.origin, ent->s.origin);
4752  VectorCopy(cl.ps.viewangles, ent->s.angles);
4753  // copy session data, so we spawn in as the same class
4754  // save items
4755  saved = client->pers;
4756  sess = client->sess;
4757  Com_Memcpy(persistant, ent->client->ps.persistant, sizeof(persistant));
4758  // give them the right weapons/etc
4759  *client = cl;
4760  client->sess = sess;
4761  client->sess.playerType = ent->client->sess.latchPlayerType = cl.sess.playerType;
4762  client->sess.playerWeapon = ent->client->sess.latchPlayerWeapon = cl.sess.playerWeapon;
4763  client->sess.playerWeapon2 = ent->client->sess.latchPlayerWeapon2 = cl.sess.playerWeapon2;
4764  // spawn them in
4765  ClientSpawn(ent, qfalse, qtrue, qtrue);
4766  // restore items
4767  client->pers = saved;
4768  Com_Memcpy(ent->client->ps.persistant, persistant, sizeof(persistant));
4769  client->ps = cl.ps;
4770  client->ps.clientNum = ent->s.number;
4771  ent->health = client->ps.stats[STAT_HEALTH];
4772  SetClientViewAngle(ent, cl.ps.viewangles);
4773  // make sure they dont respawn immediately after they die
4774  client->pers.lastReinforceTime = 0;
4775 }
